{"TopicId":132969,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"KSP Perlin Noise Planet Generation.","CreatedByName":"Matuchkin","CreatedById":135127,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-26T17:03:13Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Matuchkin","CreatedById":135127,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-26T17:03:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerlin noise is a type of gradient noise (I\u0027m not going to act like I\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Efully\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0understand that term) used to generate 3-dimensional terrains.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy point here is this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EHere\u0027s a mountain range on Kerbin:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.pinterest.com/thibstars/kerbal-space-program/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022border:0px;color:rgb(102,0,153);font-family:arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:0px;text-align:center;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(241,241,241);\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00229fed844f7e1ecd815169ae8f50e182e5.jpg\u0022 height=\u0022177\u0022 src=\u0022https://s-media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com/236x/9f/ed/84/9fed844f7e1ecd815169ae8f50e182e5.jpg\u0022 style=\u0022border:0px;margin-top:111px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);background-position:0px 10px;\u0022 width=\u0022236\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EAnd here\u0027s a mountain range generated via \u003Cu\u003ETerragen 0.9.19\u003C/u\u003E\u00A0using\u00A0perlin noise:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Ca href=\u0022http://libnoise.sourceforge.net/examples/complexplanet/images/mountainmed.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022font-family:verdana, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333330154419px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022River valleys\u0022 src=\u0022http://libnoise.sourceforge.net/examples/complexplanet/images/thumbs/mountainmed.jpg\u0022 style=\u0022border-style:none;padding:4pt;background-color:#FFFFFF;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile the top screenshot displays a streched out, abnormally sharp and smooth terrain, the bottom screenshot (generated via\u00A0Terragen 0.9.19) displays an actual mountain/valley range.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd here\u0027s the capabilities of the present version of Terragen- Terragen 3. Enjoy:\u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.lejbs.com/?projects=terragen-3-experiments\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022border:0px;color:rgb(102,0,153);font-family:arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:0px;text-align:center;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(241,241,241);\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Terragen_003.jpg\u0022 height=\u0022398\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.lejbs.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Terragen_003.jpg\u0022 style=\u0022border:0px;margin-top:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);background-position:0px 10px;\u0022 width=\u0022708\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.astrosurf.com/luxorion/terragen-rendering-time.htm\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022border:0px;color:rgb(102,0,153);font-family:arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:0px;text-align:center;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(241,241,241);\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022sthelens-4k-reg.jpg\u0022 height=\u0022398\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.astrosurf.com/luxorion/Sciences/sthelens-4k-reg.jpg\u0022 style=\u0022border:0px;margin-top:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);background-position:0px 10px;\u0022 width=\u0022796\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E \u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.creativeobserver.com/news/terragen-3-2.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022border:0px;color:rgb(102,0,153);font-family:arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:0px;text-align:center;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(241,241,241);\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00225216_planetside_software_terragen_3_exam\u0022 height=\u0022398\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.creativeobserver.com/img/5216_planetside_software_terragen_3_example_lg.jpg\u0022 style=\u0022border:0px;margin-top:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);background-position:0px 10px;\u0022 width=\u0022597\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://michieldb.nl/terragen/continue.htm\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022border:0px;color:rgb(102,0,153);font-family:arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:0px;text-align:center;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(241,241,241);\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022pilbara-4-3---rerender-2013-v2.jpg\u0022 height=\u0022398\u0022 src=\u0022http://michieldb.nl/terragen/2013/pilbara-4-3---rerender-2013-v2.jpg\u0022 style=\u0022border:0px;margin-top:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);background-position:0px 10px;\u0022 width=\u0022708\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m asking here if it is possible to generate Kerbin (and all the other planets in the Kerbol system)\u00A0via perlin noise, and somehow replace the present Kerbin with the improved one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy the way, the second screenshot from Terragen 0.9.19 is actually a generation of Kerbin. The SQUAD developers got the idea for Kerbin after looking at that planet\u00A0model. Here\u0027s a link:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://libnoise.sourceforge.net/examples/complexplanet/index.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://libnoise.sourceforge.net/examples/complexplanet/index.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think this is an important topic, concerning the replacement/ improvement of the game graphics. So, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266485\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0022\u003E@SQUAD\u003C/a\u003E, come \u0027ere and see for yourself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, and for all you volumetric-cloud modders, here\u0027s something to work on:\u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022http://community.thefoundry.co.uk/discussion/topic.aspx?f=4\u0026amp;t=78032\u0026amp;page=3\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022border:0px;color:rgb(102,0,153);font-family:arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:0px;text-align:center;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(241,241,241);\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00228205ff6c295370deb4d9f63d849ac77e.jpg\u0022 height=\u0022398\u0022 src=\u0022http://s3.amazonaws.com/forums.content.luxology.com/images/full/8205ff6c295370deb4d9f63d849ac77e.jpg\u0022 style=\u0022border:0px;margin-top:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);background-position:0px 10px;\u0022 width=\u0022796\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso generated via perlin noise (Terragen 3).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-26T17:06:12Z\u0022 title=\u002202/26/2016 05:06  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Matuchkin\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Matuchkin","CreatedById":135127,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-26T17:34:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hope I\u0027m understood, I kind of got lost while writing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-26T17:41:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile the pics look very nice I have enough trouble with performance with the current terrain.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NathanKell","CreatedById":75006,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-26T22:12:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUh...KSP already uses perlin noise. Also some other fractal algorithms. It\u0027s not a magic wand. :]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want to learn how KSP\u0027s terrain system works, check this video out:(second half, with Mike)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/mXTxQko-JH0?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}